  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add minced garlic and cook for about 1 minute until fragrant, stirring frequently to prevent burning.",
    "Pour soymilk into the pan with the garlic. Stir continuously to avoid curdling.",
    "Gradually whisk in soy sauce and cornstarch mixture until a thick sauce forms. Reduce heat to low and simmer for another 2-3 minutes.",
    "Garnish with scallions, add sprouts and vegetables last when reheating the soymilk mixture.",
    "Serve hot over rice or noodles."
  ],
